name: Fidus Style LoRA
description:
This LoRA was trained on the works of German art nouveau and symbolist painter and illustrator Hugo Reinhold Karl Johann Höppener (1868 - 1948), better known as Fidus ("The Faithful"), the name awarded to him bis mentor Karl Wilhelm Diefenbach:

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fidus

The LoRA is capable of generating images very faithful (no pun intended) to Fidus's original works and style, but also suitable for other, more experimental aesthetical generations.

I hope you find this ressource useful, and hopefully, I could rouse your interest and awareness for this rather obscure and lesser known artist.

modelVersions.description: The first, initially unpublished version of the Fidus LoRA. Compared to version 2.0, which I consider to be the definitive one, its results are a bit less faithful to Fidus's original works and style. It is still very capable when it comes to generating beautiful, aesthetically pleasing images, though.
